&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Midwife Antenatal Clinic and Day Assessment Unit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for dynamic enthusiastic Band 6 Midwives to join our team within Antenatal clinic at Buckinghamshire NHS Trust. This role will have a focus &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicants will be motivated, passionate and dedicated to providing high quality women-centred care. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will work collaboratively within our multidisciplinary team supporting woman and their families though their pregnancy journey.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your experience will ensure that you provide a high standard of care to our mothers and their families. As a member of our team you will be professional, reliable, safe and compassionate and have excellent communication skills and a progressive attitude to the continual improvement of patient care through evidence based practice. Minimum hours per week : 22.5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Hours will be based across sites at Stoke Mandeville and Wycombe Hospitals. The Service is open between 8-6 pm Monday – Sunday and the successful applicant will undertake a variety of shifts between these opening times to ensure the clinics is covered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is recruited on a rotational basis which may require the post holder to work in all areas of maternity and cover all shifts.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
